<br>
NOW...I also put Malle and Range attack, the sit/stand, camp, time and who on hot buttons.  <br>
<br>
...okay first let me explain WHAT I want to do in order to NOT do something (make sense?).<br>
<br>
The other day, I still had my dagger and torch in my hand and went to Yrin for a quest.  He asked if I wanted to make...blah, blah, blah...I wanted to say &quot;art keepers gloves please&quot;  in reply to him.  Well, I hit &quot;A&quot; and he killed me (because THAT is the attack key and I wasn't IN the chat line box WHERE you type).  I actually didn't realize what I did until AFTER I came back to life and scrolled up.  <br>
<br>
NOW, I put my dagger and wisp in a bag when I go inside...BUT then I sometimes forget to put it BACK in the primary and secondary spot...UNTIL I am in a fight and see no little dagger over the malle button when I go to push it.<br>
<br>
SO...now that I have Melle attack on a hot button (as opposed to that button that it comes on).  IF I do the Options-Macro-Keyboard thing to CHANGE the key for my malle HOT button to say...&quot;=&quot; will the &quot;A&quot; still trigger my REGULAR (non-hot button) malle button?  OR will I then be free of accidentally attacking people if I have my dagger in primary...thus the &quot;=&quot; on hot button over-riding the &quot;A&quot; on the regular malle button? <br>
<br>
*edit*  BTW, That hot button is pre-set on either 0 or 1 (the malle attack is on my first hot button).  But I don't want it there either for when I type a number getting/selling QUANTITY of stuff to merchants or rearranginf stuff AS I talk to someone in front of me, etc. <p><center><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaSig.gif"><br><br><b><font face="garamond" size=3><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543802">My Magelo Profile</a></center><font size=0 font face=garamond font color=black></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/16/03 2:10:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 2:12:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: This might be a stupid question...but</span><hr size=1> You'll still need to remap the button in the Keyboard options screen.  In the window selector, press &quot;options&quot;, then choose the Keyboard tab.  There is a drop-down box with different options, and I think that auto attack is in under combat.<br>
<br>
Anyway, it will still be mapped to &quot;a&quot; until you change it.  I changed it to ~.<br>
<br>
The auto attack mapping was responsible for my first death ever.  As a wood-elf ranger, I vowed not to die.  When I first popped into Kelethin, I was inside the Ranger Guild building.  I hailed the first guy I saw, and when I went to reply, I must of hit &quot;a&quot;.  He killed me quick, and I woke up in the middle of Greater Faydark.  It took me 30 minutes to find the ranger guild again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 800<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 2:13:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: This might be a stupid question...but</span><hr size=1> The 'melee attack' button you moved from your Actions window to your Hot Buttons window is only triggered by hitting whatever number slot you put it in.<br>
<br>
Once you remap the autoattack away from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>A</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, there is no longer any danger of accidentally attacking when you hit the A button. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
