<br>
It also sounds like you have a hotbutton (the buttons in the bottom left usually) set to melee attack also.  Binding your ='s key to auto attack will Not impact your hotbutton in any way.  It will be good to know however that your hotbuttons are activated by the number keys on top of your keyboard.  So if you have Melee attack in the top left hotbutton, pressing the 1 key will start you attacking.  <br>
<br>
Once you get the hang of it though, you'll always remember to press enter before you talk to an npc.  And when you get further on in levels you can buy items that dont have a dmg/delay (like a stein) which means you wont attack even if you hit the button. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 1:22:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hotkeys</span><hr size=1> I suggest binding auto-attack to the &quot;~&quot; key, as suggested earlier.  I don't think you need mellee attack or ranged attack as a hotkey.  Just hit ~ to attack someone with your dagger.  I assume you don't actually have a ranged mellee attack to use against enemies, so you shouldn't need the ranged attack button ever.<br>
<br>
Also, many if not most magi NEVER engage in mellee attacks ever.  They always use pets and spells instead of using weapons.  At low levels you can do some ok damage using weapons (especially with a nice weapon like you have), but don't plan on doing real damage melleeing once you get much past lvl 10.<br>
<br>
<br>
For hotkeys, I always have keys for a nuke command, sit, /book 1, an assist command, the gate spell, and pet attack and back off commands. Oh, and a hotkey for casting my damage shield on my pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jayteebushwacker>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Summoner Da'FoH</span><br>  Posts: 1456<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 1:30:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hotkeys</span><hr size=1> Personally I use the number pad 0 key.  There is zero chance of me hitting that one by mistake because on my keyboard it is separated from the alpha keys by about 2 inches. <p><hr>
